<br>
&quot;Could I trouble you for a spirit of wolf please?&quot; - These guys got it every time, without charge.  For someone that polite, unless they practically forced money in my face, I didn't ask for anything.<br>
<br>
&quot;Could you SoW me please?&quot; - They said please.  They asked me directly.  Probably in a rush, no trouble.  Same as above.<br>
<br>
&quot;will pay sow plz thx&quot; - Granted, ain't roleplaying, but they asked, and offered to pay.  Problems with their choice of questioning aside, they did ask, offered to pay, to hell with it, not a problem.<br>
<br>
&quot;sow m8&quot; - followed most likely by /prod /prod /prod /prod, no fuck off.  You don't ask, you don't get.  I ain't a self filling free service station, I'm a druid who, especially at this level, takes one hell of a long time to build up mana.  Obviously I never told them to fuck off directly, but I made it clear they weren't getting anything.<br>
<br>
